# Resume API Examples - HTTP Requests

This file contains example HTTP requests for all resume endpoints. These can be executed using tools like curl, Postman, or REST Client extensions.

## Authentication
All requests require a JWT bearer token. Replace `{token}` with your actual authentication token.

---

## Core Resume Operations

### Get Resume by ID
```http
GET /api/v1/resume/01ARZ3NDEKTSV4RRFFQ69G5FAV HTTP/1.1
Host: localhost:5000
Authorization: Bearer {token}
```

### Create Resume
```http
POST /api/v1/resume HTTP/1.1
Host: localhost:5000
Authorization: Bearer {token}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "resumeName": "Software Engineer Resume",
  "userName": "John Doe",
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "role": "Software Engineer"
}
```

### Full Update (PUT)
```http
PUT /api/v1/resume/01ARZ3NDEKTSV4RRFFQ69G5FAV HTTP/1.1
Host: localhost:5000
Authorization: Bearer {token}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userName": "John Doe",
  "resumeName": "Senior Software Engineer Resume",
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "summary": "Experienced software engineer with 7+ years...",
  "role": "Senior Software Engineer",
  "order": "WorkExperience,Skills,Projects,Education,Certifications",
  "address": "San Francisco, CA",
  "phoneNumber": "+1-555-0123",
  "tags": "backend,python,go",
  "isFavourite": true,
  "linkedinUrl": "https://linkedin.com/in/johndoe",
  "githubUrl": "https://github.com/johndoe",
  "portfolioUrl": "https://johndoe.dev"
}
```

### Partial Update (PATCH) - Update Only Summary
```http
PATCH /api/v1/resume/01ARZ3NDEKTSV4RRFFQ69G5FAV HTTP/1.1
Host: localhost:5000
Authorization: Bearer {token}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "summary": "Passionate backend engineer specializing in distributed systems and microservices architecture"
}
```

### Partial Update (PATCH) - Update Multiple Fields
```http
PATCH /api/v1/resume/01ARZ3NDEKTSV4RRFFQ69G5FAV HTTP/1.1
Host: localhost:5000
Authorization: Bearer {token}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "role": "Senior Backend Engineer",
  "tags": "backend,golang,kubernetes,microservices",
  "isFavourite": true
}
```

